.TH wcslen 3 2023-02-05 "Linux man-pages 6.03"
.SH NAME
wcslen \- determine the length of a wide-character string
.SH LIBRARY
Standard C library
.RI ( libc ", " \-lc )
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <wchar.h>
.PP
.BI "size_t wcslen(const wchar_t *" s );
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR wcslen ()
function is the wide-character equivalent
of the
.BR strlen (3)
function.
It determines the length of the wide-character string pointed to
by
.IR s ,
excluding the terminating null wide character (L\[aq]\e0\[aq]).
.SH RETURN VALUE
The
.BR wcslen ()
function returns the
number of wide characters in
.IR s .
